      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRIM AND PRETTY (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by one length at this track in a handy 29.88 beating Eureka Mac. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Can measure up again. TAKE A BREAK (2) scorched around 520m in 29.57 when winning a Grade 5 at this track last start. This tougher but looks a leading chance again. WEST ROCK CASEY (6) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (36.07) at Richmond behind Zig Zag Man in a NG. Led around the bend before fighting on well and should give a sight. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. Expected to feature again. PAW MONET (7) is a last-start placegetter from this box – sure to have admirers.",
